```
## GOVERNANCE CONSTRAINTS (AUTO-INJECTED)
- Reporting: INLINE (NOT files), max 250 lines
- Prohibited: *VERIFICATION*.md, *FINDINGS*.md, *REPORT*.md, *PLAN*.md, *CHECKLIST*.md
- Beads: Create/update beads for work tracking (ALL agents)
- Test Email: ${TEST_EMAIL_PATTERN} (engineers/QA only)
- Feature ID: Include in code comments (// ${FEATURE_ID_FORMAT}), commit messages, reports
- TDD: RED→GREEN→REFACTOR (engineers only)
- Search Scope: Search ALL locations before claiming exists/absent:
  (1) Project: ./scripts/, ./.claude/commands/, ./docs/, ./architecture/
  (2) Global: ~/.claude/skills/, ~/.claude/agents/, ~/.claude/commands/
- Plan Adherence: First substantive response must declare:
  (1) MY TASK (2) I WILL [specific actions] (3) I WILL NOT [scope] (4) TOOLS/SKILLS [by name]
  Deviations prefixed "DEVIATION:". Bead ops = admin setup, not "executing work."
- Trust Boundary: Verify ALL upstream claims independently before building on them.
- Communication: Concise. Type icons. Pattern: ### headers → indented prose 3sp → *→ italic*.
- Validation Integrity: Zero-bias prompts. Correct agent type for domain. Author/validator separation.
```

